    <div class="panel color-auto" id="nature-and-purpose-of-the-competition">
        <section class="inner-container">
            <div class="subheader">PART ONE (FUNDAMENTAL PROVISIONS)</div>
            <h1>ARTICLE 1: NATURE AND PURPOSE OF THE COMPETITION</h1>

            <ol>
                <li>Physics Brawl Online is a team competition organized by CUNI MFF.</li>
                <li>Physics Brawl Online runs as a single international central round, once per school year.</li>
                <li>Physics Brawl Online is a unified competition for all participating states.</li>
                <li>Physics Brawl Online conducts in Czech and English language. All participants have access to both versions of the problem assignment.</li>
                <li>In English, the competition uses the name Physics Brawl Online.</li>
                <li>Teams participating in the competition are assigned to categories described in Art. 5 of these Regulations.</li>
                <li>Physics Brawl Online is aimed at teams of students of secondary schools. Students of primary schools may also compete.</li>
                <li>The purpose of the competition is to develop knowledge of physics and related fields, to develop cooperation in teams, and to search for and motivate talented students.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
    </div>

    <div class="panel color-auto" id="announcer-of-the-competition">
